Description: Flaring ring foot and lower body sherd of East Greek pottery closed vessel, possibly an oinochoe; white slip; exterior: lower wall reserved and orange-fired band on foot; some white slip on underside of foot; inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 369)
Johnston 2006a / Trademarks on Greek Vases: Addenda (East Greek 198) (Entry should be 197)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.443)
